    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Red as a beet\n: cutaneous vasodilation\nBlind as a bat\n: nonreactive mydriasis (often delayed 12-24hr)\nMad as a hatter\n: delirium; attention deficit; hallucinations; dysarthria; lethargy\nFull as a flask\n: urinary retention\nHot as a hare\n: anhydrotic hyperthermia (may become severe w/ agitation)\nDry as a bone\n: anhidrosis (esp axillae, mouth)\nAnd the heart runs alone\n: Tachycardia (HR 120-160) and decreased/absent bowel sounds\nECG\nSinus tachycardia\nQRS widening in some cases",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "ECG",
